# SII Agent Fleet — shared site configuration
#
# Single place to point the fleet at your own infrastructure (model gateway,
# Opik, package mirrors, container image). Most lines are commented out and
# ship with a public-safe placeholder or default. Package mirror defaults
# are uncommented below — override in config.local.env if needed.
#
# This committed template is sourced by the Harbor runner
# (Agents/utils/common/Harbor/env.sh), the OpenClaw setup
# (Agents/Openclaw/scripts/setup.sh), and the PinchBench and clawBio runners.
# An adjacent config.local.env
# (git-ignored) is sourced right after this file and overrides it. Uncommented
# values here override the built-in defaults; to override for a single run, pass
# an environment variable instead.
#
# Keep real secrets out of this committed file: put credentials (API_KEY)
# in config.local.env, or export them in your shell.

# ── Model gateway ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenAI- or Anthropic-compatible endpoint and credential. BASE_URL is the API
# root WITHOUT a version suffix; the runners append /v1 (or /v1/chat/completions)
# as needed, so a URL already ending in /v1 also works.
# BASE_URL=https://api.example.com
# API_KEY=sk-your-key
# MODEL=your-model-id

# ── Opik tracing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPIK_URL=https://opik.example.com/api
# OPIK_PROJECT_NAME=

# ── Package mirrors ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Override these to use private or regional mirrors.
PIP_INDEX_URL=https://pypi.org/simple/
# PIP_EXTRA_INDEX_URL=
# PIP_TRUSTED_HOST=
NPM_CONFIG_REGISTRY=https://registry.npmjs.org
GO111MODULE=on
GOPROXY=https://goproxy.cn,direct
GOSUMDB=sum.golang.google.cn
RUSTUP_UPDATE_ROOT=https://mirrors.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/rustup/rustup
RUSTUP_DIST_SERVER=https://mirrors.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/rustup
CARGO_REGISTRY_REPLACE_WITH=mirror
CARGO_REGISTRY_URL=sparse+https://mirrors.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/crates.io-index/
